\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Feb 03, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104prv1665702740862.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/prv1665702740862.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/prv1665702740862.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"prv1665702740862\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">$PRIV_MON_USER\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specify the privileged user account under which the Uniface Router runs and which can be used to start and stop Uniface Routers and Servers using the Uniface Router Monitor or the UROUTMON component.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"prv1665702740862__topic_d142424e1_d142425e1_d142426e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"prv1665702740862__p_d142427e1_d142428e1_d142429e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$PRIV_MON_USER</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">PrivilegedUser</var></p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"prv1665702740862__p_d142430e1_d142431e1_d142432e1\">Example:\n            <code class=\"ph codeph\">$PRIV_MON_USER=urouter10</code></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"prv1665702740862__section_kvw_1jv_jwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d956010e70\">Arguments</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"prv1665702740862__p_d142436e1_d142437e1_d142438e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">PrivilegedUser</var>—user name provided for the Uniface Router account\n            during installation.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"prv1665702740862__section_cz5_cjv_jwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d956010e82\">Defaults</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"prv1665702740862__table_d17108e1_d17109e1_d17110e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Assignment file: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><span class=\"ph filepath\">urouter.asn</span>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Section: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">[SETTINGS] </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">urouter</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"prv1665702740862__section_jwd_gjv_jwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d956010e132\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"prv1665702740862__p_d142445e1_d142446e1_d142447e1\">Any user can view Uniface Routers and Servers with\n            the URouter Monitor or the UROUTMON component, but only a privileged user can start and\n            stop them. To become a privileged user you must select <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Become privileged\n               user</span> in the Connect dialog or use the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Authorize menu\n               item</span> to perform a logon as the specified user in the URouter Monitor.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"prv1665702740862__p_d142448e1_d142449e1_d142450e1\">When using the UROUTMON component this logon must\n            be done using the <span class=\"keyword apiname\">ADMLOGON</span> operation.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"prv1665702740862__note_lcb_3jv_jwb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Ensure that you protect the\n               <span class=\"ph filepath\">urouter.asn</span> file with appropriate privileges to prevent\n            non-authorized users from changing this setting.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531051\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531051\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$PRIV_MON_USER Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Feb 03, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 $PRIV_MON_USER Specify the privileged user account under which the Uniface Router runs and which can be used to start and stop Uniface Routers and Servers using the Uniface Router Monitor or the UROUTMON component. $PRIV_MON_USER = PrivilegedUser Example: $PRIV_MON_USER=urouter10 Arguments PrivilegedUser —user name provided for the Uniface Router account during installation. Defaults Assignment file: urouter.asn Section: [SETTINGS] Default value: urouter Description Any user can view Uniface Routers and Servers with the URouter Monitor or the UROUTMON component, but only a privileged user can start and stop them. To become a privileged user you must select Become privileged user in the Connect dialog or use the Authorize menu item to perform a logon as the specified user in the URouter Monitor. When using the UROUTMON component this logon must be done using the ADMLOGON operation. Note: Ensure that you protect the urouter.asn file with appropriate privileges to prevent non-authorized users from changing this setting. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}